\subsection{Background parameterization}
\label{sec:bkg_pPb}

\subsubsection{\PW+jets background}
\label{sec:bkg_Wjets}

The MC simulation is used to seed the parameters of the \PW+jets background modeling. 
Once a functional form is derived, its parameters and normalization are determined from the fit to the data. 
This approach is justified on the grounds of the nonaccurate simulation in the phase space of the analysis, i.e, 
simulations rely on the \PYTHIA parton shower to predict most of the jets in the \ttbar\ signal region. 
Therefore the simulation could bias both the rate and the shape of \PW+heavy flavor production.

From the MC simulation, a Landau pdf~\cite{roofit} is found to describe reasonably well the contribution from \PW+jets in all mass variables. 
Figure~\ref{fig:wparammc} compares the \PW{}+jets simulated events with the Landau pdf fit superimposed. 
Because of the low event count, the fit is performed using events with no \cPqb-tagged jets; a fair agreement is observed between the pdf and the simulation. 
It can also be noticed that the Landau parameters differ only slightly with respect to those obtained for the wrong assignment component of the signal, 
as described in the previous Section and shown in the same Figure. This is not surprising given the combinatorial nature of the \PW+jets background.

\begin{figure}[!ht]
\centering
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/mjj_mu1l4j2q_w}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/mthad_mu1l4j2q_w}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/mtlep_mu1l4j2q_w}}
\caption[Parametrized \PW+jets spectra for the dijet invariant mass, and hadronic and leptonic top mass in the $\mu$+jets final state at $\rootsNN=8.16$\,\TeV]
{Simulated and parametrized \PW+jets spectra in the $\mu$+jets final state as a function of \mjj (a), $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{had}}}$ (b) and $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{lep}}}$ (c)
in the 1$\ell$4j0\cPqb event category; their difference, divided by the statistical uncertainty in the simulation, is represented on the top panels. 
The superimposed gray curve corresponds to the parametrized contribution from wrong assignments in the \ttbar\ signal process~\citeAN{AN-17-043}.
}
\label{fig:wparammc}
\end{figure}

The higher event count \PW+jets LO sample using pp collisions at 8\,\TeV\ validates the Landau parameterization. 
Figure~\ref{fig:wshapevar} shows the relative difference in the shape of the three mass distributions in the $1\ell$4j1\cPqb and $1\ell$4j2\cPqb 
with respect to the $1\ell$4j0\cPqb event category. 
The largest deviations are seen for \mjj and $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{lep}}}$ variables. 
The former indicates that the kinematics of the jets in a heavy-flavor enriched region are harder with respect to the light-flavor region, 
while the latter is expected as \cPqb-jets tend to contribute to real \ptmiss through semileptonic \cPqb quark decays.

\begin{figure}[!ht]
\centering
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mjj_refratios}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mthad_refratios}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mtlep_refratios}}
\caption[Simulated \PW+jets spectra for the dijet invariant mass, and hadronic and leptonic top mass in the $\ell$+jets final state using pp collisions at $\sqrt{s}=8$\,\TeV]{
  Relative difference of the \PW+jets spectra in the $1\ell$4j1\cPqb and $1\ell$4j2\cPqb with respect to the 1$\ell$4j0\cPqb event category from the \PW+jets LO sample,
  using pp collisions at 8\,\TeV. 
  The ratios are shown for the \mjj (a), $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{had}}}$ (b) and $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{lep}}}$ (c) variables. 
  The gray band illustrates the statistical uncertainty in the MC sample using events in the 1$\ell$4j0\cPqb event category, 
  while the red lines represent first order polynomial fits to the ratios~\citeAN{AN-17-043}.
}
\label{fig:wshapevar}
\end{figure}

The relative differences in Fig.~\ref{fig:wshapevar}, as extracted using pp collisions, are used to extrapolate the \PW+jets distributions from the $1\ell$4j0\cPqb 
to the $1\ell$4j1\cPqb and $1\ell$4j2\cPqb event categories; each simulated \PYTHIA event falling in the $1\ell$4j0\cPqb category is reweighted according to the value of the relative difference. 
The extrapolated distributions are fitted to Landau functions and are further compared to events from the \PYTHIA MC simulation. 
The obtained results are shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:wshapepred}. 
Within the limited statistical accuracy of this procedure, the Landau parameterization is indeed expected to be a good approximation of the \PW+jets contribution in the different event categories. 
However, as summarized in Table~\ref{tab:wlanparams}, the parameters seem to differ in each category, 
and hence motivating separate width ($\sigma$) and most probable value (MPV) Landau parameters per category. 
It is though interesting to note that the $\sigma/\textrm{MPV}$ ratio is approximately the same possibly indicating that the intrinsic resolution is approximately the same. 
In the fit to the data Gaussian penalty terms are assigned to allow for a 5 (20)\% variation in the  $\sigma$ (MPV) with respect to the predictions in Table~\ref{tab:wlanparams}.

\begin{figure}[!ht]
\centering
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mjj_extrapolation}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mthad_extrapolation}}
\subfloat[][]{\includegraphics[width=0.32\textwidth]{figures/pPb8TeV/w_mtlep_extrapolation}}
\caption[Reweighted and fitted \PW+jets spectra for the dijet invariant mass, and hadronic and leptonic top mass in the $\ell$+jets final state using pPb collisions at $\rootsNN=8.16$\,\TeV]{
Reweighted \PW+jets spectra in the different event categories based on the ratio (Fig.~\ref{fig:wshapevar}) calculated from the \PW+jets LO sample, using pp collisions at 8\,\TeV 
separately for the \mjj (a), $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{had}}}$ (b) and $m_{\cPqt_{\textrm{lep}}}$ (c) variables. 
Landau functions are fitted to the reweighted spectra, while the latter are further compared to events from the \PYTHIA MC simulation (Table~\ref{tab:mc_pPb8TeV}), using pPb collisions~\citeAN{AN-17-043}. 
}
\label{fig:wshapepred}
\end{figure}

